Sure, here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "obali" in different forms and positions, with the starred word highlighted:

1. *Obali* sam čamac na obalu reke. (*Obali* - imperative verb form meaning "shore" or "beach". Translation: I am shoring the boat on the riverbank.)
2. Ova kuća se nalazi na *obali* mora. (*Obali* - noun in locative case meaning "coast" or "shore". Translation: This house is located on the seaside.)
3. Našli smo se na *obali* reke i pecali ribe. (*Obali* - noun in prepositional case meaning "shore" or "bank". Translation: We met on the riverbank and fished for fish.)
4. *Obalila* se kiša i svi smo se pokvasili. (*Obalila* - past tense verb form meaning "to pour down" or "to fall heavily". Translation: It rained heavily and we all got wet.)
5. Našao sam staru fotografiju *obaljenu* u prašinu. (*Obaljenu* - past participle of the verb "obaliti" meaning "to cover with dust" or "to dust off". Translation: I found an old photograph covered in dust.)
6. Kada se *obalim* na kauč, ne mogu da se ustajem satima. (*Obalim* - first person singular present tense of the verb "obaliti" meaning "to lie down" or "to lounge". Translation: When I lie down on the couch, I can't get up for hours.)
7. *Obale* reka su pune biljnog i životinjskog sveta. (*Obale* - plural noun in nominative case meaning "shores" or "banks". Translation: The riverbanks are full of plant and animal life.)
8. Stado ovaca se *obalilo* u hladovinu drveta. (*Obalilo* - past tense verb form meaning "to lie down" or "to rest". Translation: The flock of sheep lay down in the shade of the tree.)